HEADWORD: Harmonite
<hw>Har"mo*nite</hw> <pr>(-n⟦imac⟧t)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a religious
sect, founded in W⟦uum⟧rtemburg in the last century, composed of
followers of <person>George Rapp</person>, a weaver. They had all their
property in common. In 1803, a portion of this sect settled in
Pennsylvania and called the village thus established, Harmony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmonium</ent>⟦br⟧
